Task 1: NSE Script Categories and Service Detection
Step 1: Explore NSE Script Categories
List and understand available NSE script categories:

# View all NSE categories
nmap --script-help all | grep "Categories:" | sort | uniq

# Examine specific categories
nmap --script-help vuln
nmap --script-help discovery
nmap --script-help auth

# Create organized results directory
mkdir -p ~/lab6_results/nse_scans
Step 2: Perform Service Detection Scanning
Execute comprehensive service detection:

# Basic service version detection with default scripts
nmap -sV -sC 127.0.0.1 -oA ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/service_scan

# Detailed banner grabbing on common ports
nmap --script=banner,ssh-hostkey,http-headers 127.0.0.1 -p 22,80,443 \
  -oN ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/banner_scan.txt

# HTTP service enumeration
nmap --script=http-enum,http-methods,http-title 127.0.0.1 -p 80,443,8080 \
  -oA ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/http_scan
Step 3: Vulnerability Assessment with NSE
Run vulnerability detection scripts:

# General vulnerability scan
nmap --script=vuln 127.0.0.1 -oA ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/vuln_scan

# SSL/TLS specific checks
nmap --script=ssl-enum-ciphers,ssl-cert,ssl-known-key 127.0.0.1 -p 443 \
  -oN ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/ssl_scan.txt

# Authentication testing (safe scripts only)
nmap --script=auth 127.0.0.1 -p 21,22,23,25 \
  -oA ~/lab6_results/nse_scans/auth_scan
